# Express + TypeScript

This project uses Express.js with TypeScript. Follow the skills:
- `.agents/skills/express-rest-api`
- `.agents/skills/nodejs-backend-patterns`

## Structure

```
src/
  config/        # env vars, DB connections
  middleware/    # auth, error handler, validation, logging
  routes/       # Router per resource
  services/     # Business logic (framework-agnostic)
  models/       # Mongoose models
  types/        # TypeScript type extensions
  utils/        # Errors, response helpers
  app.ts        # Express factory
  server.ts     # Entry point
```

## Conventions

- Use `async/await` everywhere, never callbacks
- Validate requests with Zod via `validateRequest` middleware
- Throw `AppError` subclasses (`NotFoundError`, `ValidationError`, etc.) ‚Äî the global error handler catches them
- Use `ApiResponse.success()` / `.created()` / `.paginated()` / `.error()` for consistent responses
- Organize routes per resource: `src/routes/{resource}/index.ts`
- Keep controllers thin ‚Äî delegate to service layer
- Use `authenticate` middleware on protected routes
- Extend `Express.Request` in `src/types/express.d.ts` for custom properties
